African New Year Celebration Landing Page
Overview
The African New Year Celebration Landing Page is a vibrant and responsive web interface designed to celebrate the African New Year. It features cultural motifs, a dynamic hero section, popup modals, a language toggle, and a contact form. This page is styled with TailwindCSS and includes interactive JavaScript functionality.

Features
Hero Section:
A visually striking hero section with:

A greeting title: "Happy New Year!"
Subheading and description.
A "Learn More" button for further engagement.
Language Toggle:

Easily switch between English (EN) and Russian (RU) with dynamic translations.
Popup Modal:

A popup showcasing the New Year celebration details.
Includes an image and a "Learn More" button.
Interactive Modals:

About Modal: Details about the African New Year celebration.
Events Modal: Lists upcoming events with descriptions.
Contact Modal: A functional contact form.
Responsive Design:

Mobile-friendly layout using TailwindCSS.
Content adapts seamlessly to various screen sizes.
Footer with Social Media Links:

Links to email, LinkedIn, WhatsApp, GitHub, and Instagram.
File Structure
index.html: The main HTML file for the landing page.
style.css: Contains custom styles.
script.js: Includes JavaScript for interactivity (language toggle, modals, etc.).
images/: A folder containing the African logo, popup poster, and other images.
Usage Instructions
Setup the Files:

Ensure all files (index.html, style.css, script.js, and the images/ folder) are in the same directory.
Install Dependencies:

This project uses TailwindCSS and Font Awesome:
TailwindCSS is loaded via CDN:
https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/tailwindcss/2.2.19/tailwind.min.css
Font Awesome icons are included from:
https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.5.0/css/font-awesome.min.css
Preview the Page:

Open the index.html file in any modern browser.
Language Toggle:

Click on ðŸ‡¬ðŸ‡§ EN or ðŸ‡·ðŸ‡º RU at the top-right corner to switch languages dynamically.
View Popups and Modals:

Explore the New Year Popup by interacting with the "Learn More" button.
Click navigation links in the footer to open modals like "About," "Events," or "Contact."
Contact Form:

Submit inquiries via the contact form. The form fields include Name, Email, and Message.

Check the Output folder for results of the code.